{
  "stem": "3360.3",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Because the last time we had gone there, they-- there was a whole large group of SS people at the-- that restaurant.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And, and we sat outdoors.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "It was just a wonderful thing, wonderful place to go.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And then my father had the feeling that they were staring him down.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And he no longer wanted to go there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And so all in all, and more and more, Jews were totally disowned.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Jews were totally disowned of everything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The-- I don't know if this was just before or right after we had left, my uncle in Wattenscheid, who had inherited the building that my grandfather built-- and the business, had to sold it-- had to sell it to a Gentile, to a butcher down the street, who always had had his eyes on it, for next to nothing.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And then-- and then the money was put in an account, which the government overlooked.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And they could only withdraw certain small amounts for absolute necessities.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And that's how it was with all Jews.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And-- the, the, the vice got tighter and tighter.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And you knew that, eventually, they would start a war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And it's just-- excuse me-- just a feeling that I had.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "In fact, before we left in May of 1939, I made a visit to Berlin to see my aunt and uncle once more, who had been so wonderful to me when I was four years old.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And they showed me the city.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And they showed me, they-- they-- the castle and Potsdam and went all around.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "I mean, I had been four years old.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And I was then 15.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And I went-- I went on the train myself to Berlin and back.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
